modules.description: Provides operations for parsing, validating, and serializing binary data formats using bit-level manipulation and custom type definitions. Works with byte arrays, bitfields, and structured records represented as tuples and variants. Used to process network protocol packets and embedded system data streams with precise control over memory layout.

The module provides operations for constructing and manipulating binary decision diagrams (BDDs), including logical operations like negation, conjunction, disjunction, and conditional selection, along with node traversal and variable management. It works with BDD nodes represented by the type `t`, enabling tasks such as existential and universal quantification, support extraction, and logical transformations. These capabilities are applicable in formal verification and logic synthesis, where efficient representation and manipulation of Boolean functions are critical.
